items.title: Pedroia exits after fouling ball off his face
items.summary: Red Sox second baseman Dustin Pedroia had to leave Monday night's game against the Orioles in the top of the fourth inning after he hit a foul into the ground that caromed up and hit him in the face.
items.content: Red Sox second baseman Dustin Pedroia had to leave Monday night's game against the Orioles in the top of the fourth inning after he hit a foul into the ground that caromed up and hit him in the face.

items.title: Olson hits No. 22, homers in 4th straight game
items.summary: Athletics rookie Matt Olson has homered in four consecutive games after hitting a two-run shot in the third inning Monday at Detroit for his 22nd of the season.
